Name: BPC-157
Description: BPC-157 is a synthetic peptide derived from a naturally occurring protein found in the stomach. Commonly studied for regenerative capabilities in soft tissue and gut models.

Name: GHK-CU
Description: GHK-Cu is a copper peptide studied for collagen production, skin remodeling, and wound healing; anti-inflammatory and antioxidant effects.

Name: GLP-2 (T*)
Description: GLP-2 (T*) is a dual-action peptide designed to improve glucose control and support weight loss; research suggests enhanced insulin sensitivity and metabolic health.

Name: GLP-3 (R*)
Description: GLP-3 (R*) targets multiple metabolic pathways for glucose regulation and weight management; research indicates improved insulin sensitivity and metabolic function.

Name: Tesamorelin
Description: Tesamorelin is a GHRH analog that stimulates endogenous growth hormone. Research supports benefits in abdominal fat reduction and metabolic health.
